      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Thou shalt bestow that money.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The Jews were very particular in not permitting the second tithe to be expended upon anything not permitted here. The rules as to its disposal form a separate treatise in the Talmud, called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ma’aser Shênî, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“second tithe.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or for strong drink.—From this it is clear that the use of strong drink is not sinful in itself. The same word appears in its Greek form (Heb., shêcar; Greek, sikêr) in Luke 1:15.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Or for strong drink.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—From this it is clear that the use of strong drink is not sinful in itself. The same word appears in its Greek form (Heb., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "shêcar; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Greek, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "sikêr",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
